headline: Why Dollar General (DG) Stock Is Falling Today
summary: Shares of discount retailer Dollar General (NYSE:DG) fell 4.6% in the morning session after the stock was flagged as being in "overbought" territory, signaling a potential pullback. The decline followed a significant rally where the stock had soared 21.5% over the previous three months. This rapid increase pushed a key technical indicator, the Relative Strength Index (RSI), to extreme levels, which suggested that buying momentum may have been exhausted. headline: Has Dollar General’s 75% 2025 Rally Already Priced In Its Recovery Story?
summary: If you are wondering whether Dollar General is finally a bargain after a rough few years, or if the market has already priced in the recovery story, this breakdown will help you think through whether the current share price makes sense. After a painful multi year slide, the stock has roared back recently, climbing 20.9% over the last week, 33.4% over the past month, and 75.0% year to date, even though 3 year and 5 year returns remain deeply negative.
